description: TEHRAN- The Iranian embassy in London has released a statement on X, asserting that Iranians have consistently aligned themselves with the principles of justice throughout history.
title: Iranian embassy in London reaffirms nation's enduring commitment to justice

description: TEHRAN - The Israeli military has announced the death of five more soldiers during combat in southern Lebanon.
title: Israeli losses in Lebanon rise

description: TEHRAN - Recent reports by CNN and The New York Times expose a horrifying reality: the Israeli military's systematic use of Palestinian detainees as human shields in Gaza. Investigations, drawing on testimonies from former detainees, Israeli soldiers, and eyewitnesses, paint a chilling picture of widespread and systematic exploitation of Palestinian civilians, a blatant violation of international law that constitutes a war crime by definition.
title: “Mosquito Protocol”: Israel uses Palestinian captives as human shields, CNN and NYT report

description: BEIRUT - In a bid to hide the genocidal massacres that are being committed daily in various Lebanese regions, the pro-resistance media is now the major target of the Zionist regime’s aggression after it has miserably failed to achieve a sole strategic achievement.
title: War on truth: Resistance media in crosshairs of Zionist aggression

description: The UN human rights chief on Friday said Israel's practices in northern Gaza could amount to "atrocity crimes and crimes against humanity."
title: UN rights chief: ‘Darkest moment’ of war unfolding in northern Gaza

description: TEHRAN – The BRICS bloc, once a club of five, threw open its doors in 2023, inviting six new members to join its ranks: Saudi Arabia, Iran, Ethiopia, Egypt, Argentina, and the United Arab Emirates. In the beginning of 2024, Iran, Egypt, Ethiopia, and the UAE officially stepped into the BRICS fold which now represents 46% of the world's population and contributes 37% of global GDP (measured by purchasing power parity).
title: Golden opportunity

description: TEHRAN – Iran's armed forces have prepared up to 1,000 missiles for a swift response to any potential Israeli attack, a threat that has been looming for weeks, according to the New York Times.
title: 1,000 Iranian missiles ready for potential Israeli attack, says U.S. media

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian government spokesperson, Fatemeh Mohajerani, has condemned the Israeli regime's attack on a residence occupied by journalists in southern Lebanon as a war crime.
title: Iran joins global outcry over Israel’s repeated killing of journalists

description: TEHRAN – Iran's Ambassador and Permanent Representative to the United Nations, Amir Saeid Iravani, has formally demanded that the UN Security Council condemn the targeting of two Iranian citizens in Lebanon by Israeli forces.
title: Iran demands UN condemnation of Israeli targeting of Iranian citizens in Lebanon

description: TEHRAN – The spokesperson for the Iranian Foreign Ministry has strongly dismissed Israeli claims that Iran’s Embassy in Beirut has been involved in Lebanon’s Hezbollah Resistance Movement’s attacks against the regime’s positions in the occupied territories.
title: Tehran denies embassy’s involvement in Hezbollah attacks against Israel

description: TEHRAN- Israel is perpetrating back-to-back massacres in the Gaza Strip, emboldened by the latest regional trip of US Secretary of State Antony Blinken.
title: Devilish dance: Bibi butchers, Blinken bows

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Kayhan discussed the approach of the Islamic Republic to a possible war between Iran and Israel and wrote: The conflict between Iran and the Zionist regime is not just a conflict between two political entities in West Asia, and others cannot just watch it.
title: Necessary warnings were given to some regional countries

description: TEHRAN – Major General Hossein Salami, Commander-in-Chief of Iran’s Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC), issued a stern warning to Israeli leaders on Thursday, urging them to abandon reliance on defense systems like the THAAD and avoid “irrational decisions” that could hasten the downfall of their regime.
title: IRGC chief says Israel 'should not count on THAAD' to defend against potential Iranian attacks

description: TEHRAN – The body of martyr Ali Heydari, a distinguished Iranian physician and devoted aid worker, was laid to rest at the holy shrine of Imam Khomeini in Tehran.
title: Funeral ceremony held for Iranian physician martyred in Beirut

description: TEHRAN – The Leader of the Islamic Revolution and other Iranian officials has extended their sympathies towards Hashem Safieddine, a high-ranking Hezbollah member recently martyred by Israeli forces in Beirut.
title: Leader, Iranian officials honor martyred Hezbollah member Hashem Safieddine

description: BEIRUT - According to the International Organization for Migration (IOM), the Israeli war on Lebanon, which has intensified since September 23, has resulted in the displacement of more than 1.3 million people within Lebanese territory.
title: Failure to respond to Lebanon’s displacement crisis: Deliberate or just a dereliction?

description:
Ech Gallery is playing host to an exhibition of paintings by Honia Abbasi.  
Entitled “The Wind Was Blowing Against the Sycamore Tree”, the exhibit runs until November 8 at the gallery that can be found at 10 Mirza Taraj opposite Dowlat St., Shariati Ave.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN- The all-female troupe Mehregan captivated audiences at Tehran’s Vahdat Hall on Friday with their performance of ritual movements and traditional dance, designed and directed by Mehrnoush Mehrinfar, exclusively for women.
title: Mehregan ensemble takes stage at Vahdat Hall for women-only audience

description: TEHRAN- A Persian translation of French writer Yves Simon’s book “An Ordinary Man” has recently been published by Hermes Publications in Tehran.
title: “An Ordinary Man” comes to Iranian bookstores

description: TEHRAN-The 41st Tehran International Short Film Festival (TISFF) concluded on Thursday at Milad Tower, where the winners of different categories received their prizes.
title: Tehran International Short Film Festival concludes at Milad Tower

description: TEHRAN - The National Museum of Iran will organize a special exhibition of rarely seen relics at the UNESCO-registered site of Persepolis, concurrent with the 3rd International Multimedia Festival of Cultural Heritage.
title: National Museum of Iran to showcase rarely seen relics at Persepolis

description: TEHRAN – The Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts Minister Seyyed Reza Salehi-Amiri has emphasized the need to develop a five-year plan for the tourism and maintenance of Ali-Sadr Cave, a vast water-filled cavern believed to date back to the Jurassic era.
title: Tourism minister calls for five-year development plan for Ali-Sadr Cave

description: TEHRAN – The capital city of Ashgabat hosted a joint tourism festival highlighting the cultural heritage and tourism potential of Iran and Turkmenistan, underscoring the deep-rooted relationship between the two neighbors.
title: Ashgabat festival highlights Iran-Turkmenistan cultural and tourism ties

description: TEHRAN - Situated some 250 km southeast of Shahroud in eastern Semnan province, Turan Protected Area, also known as Khar Turan National Park, is a gem for nature enthusiasts and adventure travelers.
title: Discover Turan Protected Area, one of Iran’s most precious ecological sanctuaries

description: TEHRAN –According to the Metrological Organization, the country is forecast to receive less than normal rainfall and experience above-normal heat from the start of the second month of autumn (October 22) to the end of the first month of winter (January 19, 2025).
title: Less rain, warmer weather forecast for fall, winter

description: TEHRAN –The head of the Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS), Pir-hossein Kolivand, and the president of the Russian Red Cross Society (RRCS), Savchuk Pavel Olegovich, have discussed ways to develop cooperation between the two countries.
title: Iranian red crescent, Russian red cross to develop cooperation

description: TEHRAN – Energy ministers of Iran and Pakistan met and held talks on the sidelines of the Third Belt and Road Ministerial Conference held in Qingdao, China.
title: Iran, Pakistan explore avenues of cross-border energy cooperation

description: TEHRAN - Iranian tiles and ceramic producers are currently exporting 40 percent of their products to more than 50 countries in the world, the director of the Iranian Tile and Ceramics Manufacturers Union said.
title: Iran exports 40% of its ceramic, tile output

description: TEHRAN – Men and women aged above 60 constitute some 11.5 percent of Iran’s population, an official with the health ministry has said.
title: The elderly account for over 11% of Iranian population

description: TEHRAN – The 24th Iran International Electricity Exhibition (IEE 2024) kicked off at Tehran Permanent International Fairgrounds on Thursday, IRIB reported.
title: Tehran hosting intl. electricity exhibition

description: TEHRAN –The head of the Department of Environment (DOE), Shina Ansari, has announced Iran's willingness to boost cooperation with Japan in the field of environment.
title: Tehran seeks to boost environmental ties with Tokyo

description: TEHRAN- Non-oil products worth $226 million were exported from Yazd province during the first six months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-September 21), a provincial official announced.
title: Commodities worth $226m exported from Yazd province in 6 months

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Industry, Mining, and Trade Minister Mohammad Atabak has appointed Mohammad Aghajanlou as the new head of the Iranian Mines and Mining Industries Development and Renovation Organization (IMIDRO), IRNA reported.
title: IMIDRO’s new head appointed

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Deputy Energy Minister Homayoun Haeri has said the Islamic Republic is seeking to use Chinese expertise and technology to develop the country’s renewable industry, IRNA reported.
title: Iran seeks cooperation with China for developing renewables

description: TEHRAN – Iran beat Thailand 2-0 to win the title of the 3rd Asian Men’s Youth Beach Handball Championship on Friday.
title: Iran reclaim Asian Youth Beach Handball Championship title

description: A 40-year-old father of four, Eliran Mizrahi deployed to Gaza after the Hamas attack on Israel on October 7, 2023.
title: Israeli soldiers returning from Gaza war struggle with trauma and suicide: CNN
